&quot;For example this seems ok to me, because the type is on the left&quot;<p><pre><code>    auto* x = new Foo();
</code></pre>
Are you only referring to the fact that the type is noted at least once on that line?  I ask because that would not pass my code review at all 99% of the time (manually allocating memory that way.)<p>As for something like<p><pre><code>    auto x = std::move(y);
</code></pre>
I couldn&#x27;t say it is bad without seeing the context around it.  Is it a small function?  Is it obvious what y is?  Looks fine to me in most cases.
